    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Paintings that were initially exhibited in the official Paris Salon of the 18th and 19th centuries, where members of the Academie Royale de Peinture et de Sculpture would exhibit recent works. Salon paintings are most often academic in nature, and are reflective of the forum in which they were exhibited; i.e.: a competition for public and private commissions.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Schilderijen die oorspronkelijk werden tentoongesteld in de officiële Parijse Salon (in de achttiende en negentiende eeuw), waar leden van de Academie Royale de Peinture et de Sculpture nieuwe werken presenteerden. Salonschilderijen zijn meestal academisch van aard en waren bedoeld om opdrachten van overheidsinstanties of particulieren binnen te halen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gemälde, das zuerst im offiziellen Pariser Salon des 18. und 19. Jahrunderts ausgestellt war, wo Mitglieder der Académie Royale de Peinture et Sculpture neueste Werke ausstellen wollten. Salonmalereien sind meistens in ihrer Art akademisch und das Forum spiegelnd, in dem sie ausgestellt sind; das heißt: ein Wettbewerb für öffentliche und private Aufträge.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>始於十八、十九世紀的巴黎沙龍官方展覽會，由皇家繪畫暨雕刻學院(Academie Royale de Peinture et de Sculpture)院士展示作品。沙龍繪畫通常較偏向學院派風格，這點亦反映在其展覽的討論會中，例如公開與非公開的評選委任。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Pinturas que foram inicialmente exibidas no Salão de Paris dos séculos XVIII e XIX em que membros da Academia Real de Pintura e Escultura (Academie Royale de Peinture et de Sculpture) exibiam trabalhos recentes. Pinturas de salão são frequentemente acadêmicas e refletem o fórum no qual são exibidas; isto é, uma competição para comissões públicas e privadas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000179/VP-intern</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
